STRING.Context: Title of the connection properties dialog. %1 is the name of the connection.

RESOURCE.STRING: Welcome to the ECM Connection Wizard
The ECM Connection Wizard will guide you through creating a connection to a Datalink Adapter or ECM Simulator.
Connect Directly to an ECM using the Universal Serial Bus (USB) on my computer
Connect using an RP1210A compliant Datalink adapter This includes MPSI and other 3rd party adapters
Connect to a simulated ECM through a virtual port
Please select a connection that will configure INSITE to use your Datalink Adapter and computer configuration.
Please select the specific Connection Settings based on the system configuration.
Please select the configuration from the displayed list to use for your connection.

INSITE could not detect any RP1210A Drivers.
The RP1210A Datalink Adapter Drivers must be installed before a RP1210A connection can be created.

INSITE has detected a PC Operating System
that does not support USB connections.
USB connections are available for direct connection to Signature/ISX-CM870 2002 ECM's only

Select Next if you are connecting to a new Cummins ECM that supports USB communications. Please select Back or Cancel if you are not sure or know that the ECM you are connecting to does not support USB communications.
Please read the following for USB connections.
Please select the ECM simulator to connect to.
Connect using an INLINE/INLINE I/INLINE II
The information describing your connection is grouped together as an ECM Connection and labeled with a name you provide.
Please enter a name for the new connection.
Please enter a name for the new connection.
This Connection Name already exists in the Connection Selection box. Please use a different Connection Name.
Attempting to detect ports available on machine...
Attempting to detect an RP1210A-compliant Cummins adapter...
Attempting to detect an INLINE II adapter...
Attempting to detect an INLINE/INLINE I adapter...
Attempting to detect an RP1210A-compliant Non-Cummins adapter...
The ECM Connection Wizard has successfully configured the new connection.
Please select finish to exit the ECM Connection wizard.
&To make this connection active, select this box and then click Finish
To setup &another connection, select this box and then click Finish
After you close this wizard, you can use this connection at any time by selecting it from the Connections List at the bottom of the screen.
The new and the confirmatory %s Passwords are mismatched.
The Current Password is incorrect please reenter the Password
Communications to the ECM could not be established.
Trying to connect to the ECM, please wait.
The password has been entered 3 times incorrectly
The %s Password has been entered 3 times incorrectly

Communication to the ECM has been lost.
Please check the ECM keyswitch state and all cable connections.

Select Retry to retry communication to the connected ECM or Cancel to disconnect.
Connected to ECM. Calibration download in progress...
Connected to ECM. Please wait while the calibration download cancels.
Please turn the Key Switch off, and then click OK.
Action: Waiting 30 seconds before allowing for Key On
Please turn the Key Switch on, and then click OK.
Please turn the Key Switch off for 30 seconds

Error Number : 5200

Communication between the computer and datalink adapter has been lost.
Please check cables between the computer and datalink adapter for proper connection and condition.

Select Retry, Cancel or Help for additional troubleshooting steps.

Error Number : 5201

Communication between the datalink adapter and the ECM has been lost.
Please ensure the keyswitch is on, and cables between the datalink adapter and ECM are properly connected and in good condition.

Select Retry, Cancel or Help for additional troubleshooting steps.

Error Number : 5202

Communication between the computer and datalink adapter could not be established.
Please check cables between the computer and datalink adapter for proper connection and condition.

Select Retry, Auto Configure, Cancel or Help for additional troubleshooting steps.

Error Number : 5204

Communication between the datalink adapter and the ECM could not be established.

Please check for the following conditions:
The keyswitch is on.
The cables between the datalink adapter and ECM are properly connected.
The cables are in good condition.
The correct adapter type is selected.
The correct communication protocol is selected.

Select Retry, Cancel or Help for additional troubleshooting steps.

Error Number : 5023

 A connection to the ECM cannot be established or has been lost. 
Please ensure the keyswitch is on and the cables, adapter and ECM are properly connected. 

Select Retry, Auto Configure, Cancel or Help for additional troubleshooting steps.
